> You know those special sauces that make it impossible to put down your fork? Prepare to meet your new favorite. This creamy, sweet, savory, Sriracha-spiked drizzle is so good, it'll make your taste buds light up. Even better? It's paired with crispy tempura shrimp, sesame-flecked broccoli, and quick-pickled cucumbers on top of steamy rice. Don't be surprised when you find yourself swiping up every last drop... and making up excuses to make this dish again and again.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and halve @Persian Cucumber{1}(trimmed, peeled, halved lengthwise); thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. In a #small bowl{}, combine cucumber, half the @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Set aside.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and sliced), separating whites from greens.

In a second small bowl, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @apricot jam{1}, @Sriracha{1%teaspoon}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @water{1%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil; cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce}(cut into 1-inch pieces if necessary). Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, half the @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until golden brown and crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}. Carefully toss with half the scallion greens.

Meanwhile, rinse @shrimp{10%ounce}* under cold water; pat very dry with #paper towels{}. Season with @salt{}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @tempura mix{82%g}, remaining garlic powder, @cold water{1/3%cup}, and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Stir shrimp into batter until fully coated.

> TIP: If needed, add more water 1 TBSP at a time until it reaches a pancake-batter-like consistency.

Heat a ¼-inch layer of oil in a #large heavy-bottomed pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles when added to the pan, working in batches, add coated shrimp in a single layer. Cook until golden brown and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} on the first side and ~{1-2%minutes} on the second side. Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}. Immediately season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with shrimp, quick pickles (draining first), and broccoli. Drizzle shrimp with sauce; top with remaining scallion greens, remaining sesame seeds, and a pinch of @Korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste. Serve.